name: RalphFLA
text:
This location of the Crumbl cookies store is relatively new. I was not familiar with it, saw it in the shopping center, researched it and thought it sounded like a good place to visit.

Crumbls has only been around since 2017. It appears to be growing fast.

At the end of a bike ride, I stopped to try it out. It was a good decision. Their cookies are excellent.

They are served warm. For cookies, they are expensive but these are better than any other cookies I have had in a store. The chocolate chips were tasty and large, the dough was warm and the cookies were fresh.

They are also very large. One cookie should be enough for two people. But, based on experience, many of us will eat a whole one.

The cookie flavors apparently vary each day. For those who have not done so, and who like to eat cookies, give Crumbls a try.

name: Craig Andrews
text: Grossly understaffed on a random Tuesday night. The staff managed the best that they could, but they needed more help. Ordering system must be difficult to manage because there was no rhyme or reason for some waiting 15 minutes and others waiting up to 45 minutes. Online orders seemed to be sprinkled in with those waiting in store. I will say the cookies were warm as promised and tasty but out of six flavors available, two were sold out. I would only go here again if there was nobody in the store waiting in line. At one point there were 25 people inside waiting on orders to be filled. Definitely not worth the wait.

But there was no sign or info saying this one had. Made sure to ask the young lady that was helping us. She checked the ingredients and assured us it did NOT. I was thrilled. Drive back home and start eating the cookie. Then my throat starts to close up. Take a look at my "nut" free cookie and see walnuts. Called the store and brought up the issue so it wouldn't happen to someone deadly allergic and she practically brushed it off. Please start placing signs or info when a cookie contains nuts!

text:
Very pleased with every visit to Highland Gourmet Scones. I live out of the state and any time that I am in town I swing by for a scone pick up. I at first tried the mini's to distinguish which ones would be our favorite, but I have to be honest we like them all.

So we have upgraded to purchasing the large scones in a variety of flavors. A few have made it to being a fan favorite - Cherry Amaretto, Pumpkin Spice, Toasted Coconut, and Orange Cranberry. The regular size scones are a bit more moist, and have a stronger flavor.

We highly recommend them, and have not been disappointed with any of our orders!! The one time I returned home without scones..........we had a few sad faces. It is now what we look forward to when I am in town.

Plus they are a great spot for coffee!!

This has me completely baffled because she would rather loose money than provide service.
While the cookies are fantastic, I often wondered why no one has ever said "there will be a five minute wait on those" or "we'll have to bake them for you"...a cookie takes less than fifteen minutes to bake...and you ARE serving them warm...I'm beginning to wonder what the big picture behind this cookie place really is when you can't accommodate a customer at three o'clock in the afternoon. name: Bill Crawford
text:
My wife heard about The Flour Sack from her PT(knee surgery last week). Me trying to be a good husband, she told me that she would like to try so I immediately told her let's do it. We called to make our order and were both very happy with the customer service and ease of the process and selection on short notice. We were on the circle across town so we made it there in just a few minutes. I went inside and was greeted in the most cozy, comfy place I had ever been in Dothan by a very sweet, kind lady(wish I had gotten her name so I could thank her on here but too late now, thank you for you're awesome service). Our order was already prepared that quickly but the case had items my wife didn't mention so risking getting in trouble (lol not really but husband's will understand) I asked if I could add a few items and without hesitation she was ready to help me. She packaged it up, gave me a total, I paid, and left it was a wonderful all around experience. This was the simplest part of this review lol. Skip forward a few hours, we are home and have had dinner and my wife is ready to try out the cupcakes. We both had a red velvet cupcake first and we had to stop what we were doing and thinking about to take in the experience that was happening. I can not explain in words how perfect they were, texture, smell and the taste... OMG, hands down the best red velvet anything that I've ever had my entire life (I'm 33), we then had to try another one so we each tried a different one so we could taste more without eating too much and still try more because we are still both in shock of the amazing thing happening. I got a key lime cupcake and she got a birthday cake cupcake, again we both were blown away by how incredible this all was. She is actually rushing me now because I had to stop then and write this review to let anyone know, who has a sweet tooth or any reason to get a treat, this is the place to go. We will go back in future and tell everyone we know to go try it because it is that great of an all around experience start to finish. Thank you so much and we look forward to the next time.

Update to the review, this is the next day and my wife has started negotiating terms of the last cupcake because they are that amazing.

text:
I understand limiting store capacity because of the virus, but the amount of time we had to wait outside in roughly 30 degree weather almost caused us to go elsewhere... and I really wish we had. I've bought better chocolate chip cookies from Kroger in a pack of 25 for $2.50. Also I would have expected Praline Pecan ice cream to have more pecans and not be half melted before I even began to eat it. Only reason this isn't a 1 star rating is the cookies weren't terrible. If you want better cookies go to Kroger, and for a cookie ice cream sandwich go to Brusters... and for the icing filled one, just get a double doozie from the cookie place in the mall. You could probably buy all three of those and still save money too.

Oh, and they deliver but can't do to go orders? How does that even make sense?

name: Myandi Flowers-Brasher
text:
It took about 30 minutes to get my cookies (though i do live on the edge of their delivery area). The cookies were still soft and were a little warmer than room temperature. Super yummy though. I'll definitely order from them again, especially if I'm on campus.

01/18/2020 Edit: Cookies are great, the wait is not. Make sure your order AT LEAST an hour before you need the cookies. This is especially important if you live in a residential area and not downtown/on campus. Good cookies, bad wait. Delivery time 30 minutes, have been waiting an hour and still no cookies. Their storefront is less than fifteen minutes from my house. Just called, my deliver driver is biking to my apartment. The store needs to updates their delivery times to reflect their driver's speed. It's good that they're employing bikers though.

name: Danielle Hayes
text:
It was 8:30 on a Friday night and my little girl’s icecream from dinner got eaten by a family member while she was getting ready for bed. She was so upset. I wanted to end our night on a good note. I remembered seeing this cookie store downtown that night and was excited to discover they deliver.
I ordered six cookies for our family and an icecream for her. While waiting I read reviews and was waiting to have to wait a long time. Ten minutes after ordering I get a call from the store telling me my order was ready with the exception of one cookie flavor. They offered to bake me one if I wanted to wait or substitute another one and be on their way. I chose to substitute, and ten minutes later they were at my door with warm cookies and cold Icecream. My daughter loved her cookie dough icecream and my husband and I enjoyed breaking off a few pieces of cookie to try (so warm and good. Crunchy on the edges, but nice and soft/gooey in the middle) before making ourselves save them for the kids to enjoy tomorrow. FAST delivery, and a really good bad decision to make late at night.
